- 1.000%. 1.000%. Don Emilio.
<i>- Now. write this down.</i>

710
00:34:08.796 --> 00:34:10.798
[quirky music playing]

711
00:34:12.383 --> 00:34:13.634
[sighs]

712
00:34:18.222 --> 00:34:20.058
[music ends suddely]

713
00:34:20.141 --> 00:34:21.851
[Martín] Hey. don't be sad. Guillermo.

714
00:34:22.852 --> 00:34:25.354
Come on. Let's go turn this thing around.

715
00:34:28.066 --> 00:34:29.108
Let's do this.

716
00:34:29.192 --> 00:34:31.819
As you can see. this is the fax
you sent three weeks ago.

717
00:34:31.903 --> 00:34:33.571
It's your pledge to vote for Mexico.

718
00:34:33.654 --> 00:34:37.867
And this is what we sent you a week ago.
as a small token of appreciation.

719
00:34:37.950 --> 00:34:39.702
Just take this to Coca-Cola.

720
00:34:39.786 --> 00:34:42.205
and show them that you promised us
your vote a long time ago.

721
00:34:43.039 --> 00:34:46.334
- You can tamper with a fax?
- [Martín] Come on. Rogelio.

722
00:34:46.417 --> 00:34:48.586
How in the hell
would we do that. you dummy?

723
00:34:48.669 --> 00:34:49.962
[upbeat music playing]

724
00:34:50.046 --> 00:34:50.880
Morning.

725
00:34:52.131 --> 00:34:53.091
For your cause.

726
00:34:53.174 --> 00:34:54.550
Mexico?

727
00:34:55.843 --> 00:34:56.677
'86.

728
00:34:56.761 --> 00:34:57.595
[chuckles]

729
00:34:59.388 --> 00:35:01.974
You guys better pay for
my team's travel expenses too. okay?

730
00:35:02.058 --> 00:35:04.352
No. no.
There's enough money in there already.

731
00:35:04.435 --> 00:35:07.021
Martín. it's fine. I'll cover them.

732
00:35:07.105 --> 00:35:09.065
[excited chatter]

733
00:35:09.148 --> 00:35:12.860
We're supposed to celebrate
like we're winners. right. Don Guillermo?

734
00:35:12.944 --> 00:35:14.028
Let's get to work.

735
00:35:14.112 --> 00:35:15.947
[indistinct. excited chatter]

736
00:35:16.739 --> 00:35:18.074
Mm.

737
00:35:18.157 --> 00:35:19.408
Let's dance. Let's dance.

738
00:35:20.118 --> 00:35:22.745
Oh. come on!

739
00:35:23.412 --> 00:35:25.248
Bottoms up. ladies!

740
00:35:25.331 --> 00:35:31.420
[chanting] México! México!
México! México! México!

741
00:35:32.296 --> 00:35:34.257
Come on. Come on. Open up.

742
00:35:35.758 --> 00:35:38.970
[guests chanting]

743
00:35:39.053 --> 00:35:40.263
All right. no more booze!

744
00:35:40.346 --> 00:35:42.640
Because tomorrow
we gotta vote. motherfuckers!

745
00:35:42.723 --> 00:35:44.725
[festive music continues]

746
00:35:48.688 --> 00:35:51.274
USA 4 - MEX 8

747
00:35:51.357 --> 00:35:52.775
"The tournament's organization

748
00:35:52.859 --> 00:35:56.445
is regarded as a matter
of national interest

749
00:35:56.529 --> 00:35:58.990
and international responsibility."

750
00:35:59.073 --> 00:36:00.241
[knocking on door]

751
00:36:00.324 --> 00:36:01.742
Hey. what's the matter?

752
00:36:01.826 --> 00:36:03.161
It's not looking good.

753
00:36:03.244 --> 00:36:06.247
- What do you mean?
- We lost Mozambique. Egypt. and Russia.

754
00:36:06.330 --> 00:36:08.916
Come… come in.
Don't let 'em see you like this. man.

755
00:36:09.417 --> 00:36:11.169
What happened?
How the hell did we lose 'em?

756
00:36:11.252 --> 00:36:13.462
Kissinger offered Egypt
ballistic missiles.

757
00:36:13.546 --> 00:36:15.923
gave Mozambique a donation
three times the size of ours.

758
00:36:16.007 --> 00:36:19.218
and Pelé has committed
to a dinner with Vasili Kuznetsov.

759
00:36:19.302 --> 00:36:21.137
- With what now?
- With Vasili Kuz… [sighs]

760
00:36:21.220 --> 00:36:23.431
It doesn't matter.
We're completely screwed.

761
00:36:23.514 --> 00:36:25.766
- [Susana] Wait. What happened?
- Nothing. baby. Nothing.

762
00:36:25.850 --> 00:36:29.562
Shh. Go back to sleep. Go back to sleep.
Everything's fine. You rest.

763
00:36:30.646 --> 00:36:32.773
Don Guillermo. come on. now.

764
00:36:32.857 --> 00:36:34.901
We did not come this far for nothing.

765
00:36:34.984 --> 00:36:37.528
We're gonna fix this.
You and I are gonna fix this. Understand?

766
00:36:37.612 --> 00:36:40.907
"Fix this"? We're gonna fix this?
Let me tell you what's gonna happen.

767
00:36:40.990 --> 00:36:43.075
You're gonna go.
you're gonna do your presentation.

768
00:36:43.159 --> 00:36:44.118
say all your bullshit…

769
00:36:44.202 --> 00:36:46.787
The Egyptian delegate's gonna see you
and say you're a moron.

770
00:36:46.871 --> 00:36:49.081
Then the Soviet delegate.
who's sitting next to him

771
00:36:49.165 --> 00:36:50.875
is also gonna say you're a moron.

772
00:36:50.958 --> 00:36:53.002
And then Mozambique
is also gonna say you're a moron.

773
00:36:53.085 --> 00:36:54.420
And so on and so forth.

774
00:36:54.503 --> 00:36:56.422
Everyone's gonna say you're a moron.

775
00:36:56.505 --> 00:36:59.467
just so they don't look like the moron
who didn't call you a moron.

776
00:37:01.510 --> 00:37:03.429
[energetic music rises]

777
00:37:03.512 --> 00:37:04.597
You know what?

778
00:37:05.473 --> 00:37:07.683
You and me are going to FIFA.
We have to leave right away.

779
00:37:07.767 --> 00:37:09.602
Our car will be here in 45 minutes.

780
00:37:09.685 --> 00:37:12.313
Then we'll grab a taxi. Guillermo.
Come on. Please.

781
00:37:12.396 --> 00:37:14.398
Dress sharp.
Meet you downstairs in five minutes.

782
00:37:14.482 --> 00:37:17.860
Remember. don't let 'em see you like this.
We're winning. you understand?

783
00:37:17.944 --> 00:37:20.613
We're winning. Guillermo. Five minutes.

784
00:37:20.696 --> 00:37:22.198
- Five minutes.
- Okay.

785
00:37:22.281 --> 00:37:24.450
[indistinct chatter]

786
00:37:24.533 --> 00:37:27.119
[Havelange] Ah. you're early. Guillermo.

787
00:37:27.203 --> 00:37:28.996
See you in a minute.

788
00:37:31.624 --> 00:37:33.167
[Havelange] <i>Welcome. everyone.</i>

789
00:37:33.251 --> 00:37:36.212
<i>We will listen</i>
<i>to Mexico's closing statements.</i>

790
00:37:36.295 --> 00:37:37.380
<i>Thank you.</i>

791
00:37:37.463 --> 00:37:40.049
URUGUAY - HUNGARY - AUSTRALIA - USSR

792
00:37:40.132 --> 00:37:44.679
Thank you to the president of FIFA.
João Havelange.

793
00:37:44.762 --> 00:37:46.722
Our brother. our friend.

794
00:37:46.806 --> 00:37:48.891
I'd like to begin
by reminding everyone that

795
00:37:48.975 --> 00:37:53.312
Mexico has already hosted
the World Cup before.

796
00:37:53.396 --> 00:37:56.941
And not just any World Cup.
The best World Cup in history.

797
00:37:57.024 --> 00:37:58.734
Where did they crown King Pelé?

798
00:37:58.818 --> 00:38:00.736
In Mexico 1970.

799
00:38:00.820 --> 00:38:05.574
And where. did the "Match of the Century."
as the press called it. take place?

800
00:38:05.658 --> 00:38:06.784
In my country.

801
00:38:06.867 --> 00:38:08.244
In Mexico 1970.

802
00:38:08.327 --> 00:38:10.997
And what have we been doing
in Mexico for the last 13 years?

803
00:38:11.080 --> 00:38:12.832
Growing our infrastructure.

804
00:38:12.915 --> 00:38:14.667
strengthening our organization.

805
00:38:14.750 --> 00:38:16.711
In México. we are prepared.

806
00:38:16.794 --> 00:38:18.796
We have proven that we are capable.

807
00:38:18.879 --> 00:38:21.090
and more importantly.
that we're determined.

808
00:38:21.173 --> 00:38:22.049
Let me tell you.

809
00:38:22.133 --> 00:38:25.303
I can't think of anything more important
in Mexico than football.

810
00:38:25.386 --> 00:38:29.849
So today. it's a choice
between money and love of the game.

811
00:38:29.932 --> 00:38:33.144
You will decide whether the World Cup
is hosted by a country

812
00:38:33.227 --> 00:38:34.979
that invades what it cannot buy.

813
00:38:35.062 --> 00:38:39.942
or by one where football defines us
and lives in our hearts.

814
00:38:40.026 --> 00:38:41.402
Thank you very much.

815
00:38:45.114 --> 00:38:46.741
[Havelange] Thank you. Mexico.

816
00:38:46.824 --> 00:38:49.452
[Martín] <i>Pretty good</i>
<i>revolutionary party-style speech. right?</i>

817
00:38:49.535 --> 00:38:52.997
<i>Now. while this guy talks. let me tell you</i>
<i>why I asked Guillermo</i>

818
00:38:53.080 --> 00:38:55.249
<i>to come with me to FIFA</i>
<i>before everyone else arrived.</i>

819
00:38:56.917 --> 00:39:01.505
<i>I came up with a plan to recover the votes</i>
<i>that the Americans stole from us.</i>

820
00:39:03.966 --> 00:39:06.802
<i>I made sure</i>
<i>all the delegates I knew were voting</i>

821
00:39:06.886 --> 00:39:09.347
<i>for us were seated together</i>
<i>and voted first.</i>

822
00:39:10.056 --> 00:39:13.809
<i>Or in other words. the ones</i>
<i>who were not gonna call me a moron.</i>

823
00:39:18.314 --> 00:39:21.400
Now. let's hear the votes.
please. [clears throat]

824
00:39:22.985 --> 00:39:24.070
{\an8}<i>México.</i>

825
00:39:26.781 --> 00:39:28.240
{\an8}I vote for Mexico.

826
00:39:30.326 --> 00:39:32.161
{\an8}Sweden votes for Mexico.

827
00:39:32.244 --> 00:39:38.167
[Martín] <i>So when they started hearing.</i>
<i>"Mexico. Mexico. Mexico."</i>

828
00:39:38.250 --> 00:39:39.418
{\an8}<i>The other idiots caught on.</i>

829
00:39:39.502 --> 00:39:42.630
{\an8}<i>The United States</i>
<i>might not have the majority after all.</i>

830
00:39:42.713 --> 00:39:43.798
[delegate 1] Mexico.

831
00:39:43.881 --> 00:39:45.132
[Martín] <i>Nobody wants to be</i>

832
00:39:45.216 --> 00:39:48.094
<i>the asshole that votes against the country</i>
<i>that's clearly winning.</i>

833
00:39:49.595 --> 00:39:50.429
{\an8}México.

834
00:39:51.931 --> 00:39:53.182
Mexico.

835
00:39:55.017 --> 00:39:56.769
[delegate 2] Mexico.

836
00:39:58.104 --> 00:39:59.897
{\an8}United States.

837
00:39:59.980 --> 00:40:02.274
[Havelange] Congratulations to Mexico.

838
00:40:02.358 --> 00:40:04.110
[cheering]

839
00:40:04.193 --> 00:40:06.362
[Martín] <i>Boy. did we run them</i>
<i>off the pitch.</i>

840
00:40:07.113 --> 00:40:11.283
<i>We couldn't believe it.</i>
<i>And the best part was returning to Mexico.</i>

841
00:40:11.367 --> 00:40:12.451
[plane PA chimes]

842
00:40:12.535 --> 00:40:13.536
I just can't.

843
00:40:13.619 --> 00:40:14.995
[speaking indistinctly]

844
00:40:15.079 --> 00:40:16.789
[Azcárraga laughs] <i>Hey. hey. hey!</i>

845
00:40:16.872 --> 00:40:19.625
Who screwed the gringos. you rascal. Huh?

846
00:40:19.708 --> 00:40:21.419
Who screwed the gringos?

847
00:40:21.502 --> 00:40:24.839
<i>From that moment on.</i>
<i>"El Tigre" took over the World Cup.</i>

848
00:40:24.922 --> 00:40:28.634
<i>From satellite broadcasts.</i>
<i>to whatever brand of beer would be sold.</i>

849
00:40:28.717 --> 00:40:30.136
<i>everything went through him.</i>

850
00:40:30.219 --> 00:40:32.471
- Who's got big balls. huh?
- [chuckles]

851
00:40:32.555 --> 00:40:33.931
Who's got big balls?

852
00:40:34.014 --> 00:40:36.267
[Martín] <i>It was one hell</i>
<i>of a business deal.</i>

853
00:40:36.350 --> 00:40:38.853
<i>The bonus I got was life-changing.</i>

854
00:40:38.936 --> 00:40:42.481
<i>And we finally had enough money</i>
<i>to modernize FEMEXFUT.</i>

855
00:40:42.565 --> 00:40:44.316
- [all cheering]
- [Martín] Agus!

856
00:40:44.400 --> 00:40:46.861
- You're the man. Martín.
- Thank you.

857
00:40:46.944 --> 00:40:47.862
Thank <i>you</i>.

858
00:40:47.945 --> 00:40:50.448
- So grateful. Thank you!
- [man] Ladies and gentlemen. Martín!

859
00:40:50.531 --> 00:40:52.324
Thanks. guys!

860
00:40:52.408 --> 00:40:54.452
[laughs]

861
00:40:54.535 --> 00:40:56.537
De la Torre. you son of a gun!

862
00:40:56.620 --> 00:40:58.289
Cardozo. Who said it couldn't be done?

863
00:40:58.372 --> 00:41:00.207
- Who said we couldn't?
- You're our hero!

864
00:41:00.291 --> 00:41:02.251
I'm gonna put this here. please.

865
00:41:02.751 --> 00:41:05.045
Just a second. You know what?

866
00:41:05.129 --> 00:41:07.423
Let's have a round of applause
for Mayrita.

867
00:41:07.506 --> 00:41:10.384
- Go. Mayrita!
- [cheering]

868
00:41:10.468 --> 00:41:11.302
That's right.

869
00:41:11.385 --> 00:41:15.681
Mayrita moved us into this office.
I appreciate you. Mayrita.

870
00:41:18.642 --> 00:41:21.395
I know that many of you already know this.

871
00:41:21.479 --> 00:41:25.065
but it's important to say it
and celebrate it.

872
00:41:25.149 --> 00:41:27.651
Today. it is official.

873
00:41:28.402 --> 00:41:31.447
Everyone. the 1986 World Cup is ours.

874
00:41:31.530 --> 00:41:34.325
- It will be held in Mexico!
- [all cheering]

875
00:41:34.408 --> 00:41:37.244
Thanks to you guys! Thanks to you all!

876
00:41:37.745 --> 00:41:39.121
Thank you.

877
00:41:39.205 --> 00:41:40.706
[laughs]

878
00:41:40.789 --> 00:41:44.585
We are gonna show everybody
what this country is capable of!

879
00:41:46.629 --> 00:41:49.215
This hasn't been easy.
It hasn't been easy.

880
00:41:49.298 --> 00:41:54.553
This has come at a great cost.
Even some personal sacrifice. Um…

881
00:41:55.679 --> 00:41:57.431
I expect that from all of you.

882
00:41:57.932 --> 00:42:01.143
That's what I hope.
I don't want your average workers.

883
00:42:01.894 --> 00:42:04.939
I want soldiers. [chuckles] Like Agus!

884
00:42:05.022 --> 00:42:06.106
Soldiers!

885
00:42:06.190 --> 00:42:08.901
I want soldiers! I want soldiers. dammit!

886
00:42:08.984 --> 00:42:10.611
I want you to be a soldier!

887
00:42:10.694 --> 00:42:15.241
I promise that we will deliver
the best goddamn World Cup in history!

888
00:42:15.324 --> 00:42:18.369
[cheering]

889
00:42:18.452 --> 00:42:20.621
[José Ramón] <i>The second</i>
<i>World Cup in Mexico</i>

890
00:42:20.704 --> 00:42:24.375
<i>has showcased</i>
<i>the transformative power of our nation.</i>

891
00:42:24.458 --> 00:42:27.711
<i>Telecommunications. tourism.</i>
<i>infrastructure.</i>

892
00:42:27.795 --> 00:42:30.714
<i>Economic momentum is</i>
<i>building on a grand scale.</i>

893
00:42:30.798 --> 00:42:33.759
<i>and Mexico's international rise</i>
<i>seems unstoppable.</i>

894
00:42:33.842 --> 00:42:38.597
<i>Today. the country pulses</i>
<i>with hope. pride. and national unity.</i>

895
00:42:38.681 --> 00:42:43.936
<i>The world's eyes are on Mexico.</i>
<i>drawn by the magic of football.</i>

896
00:42:44.019 --> 00:42:45.604
[Martín] <i>We were on top of the world.</i>

897
00:42:45.688 --> 00:42:48.482
<i>Being Mexican was synonymous</i>
<i>with being cool.</i>

898
00:42:48.566 --> 00:42:50.401
As the president of FEMEXFUT.

899
00:42:50.484 --> 00:42:52.695
I am honored to be
at the helm of this phenomenon

900
00:42:52.778 --> 00:42:55.239
<i>known as Mexico '86.</i>

901
00:42:55.322 --> 00:42:58.200
If the 1970 World Cup was important.

902
00:42:58.284 --> 00:43:01.120
the 1986 World Cup will be historic.

903
00:43:01.203 --> 00:43:03.872
<i>And in the middle of it all.</i>
<i>I was the man of the hour.</i>

904
00:43:03.956 --> 00:43:07.668
<i>Everyone wanted to meet me.</i>
<i>interview me. take a picture with me.</i>

905
00:43:07.751 --> 00:43:09.420
{\an8}Wonderful things keep happening.

906
00:43:09.503 --> 00:43:11.589
{\an8}The love people show me out on the street.

907
00:43:11.672 --> 00:43:14.717
{\an8}And the love I get
from the entire football community.

908
00:43:14.800 --> 00:43:20.764
The Mexican University of Sport
granted me an honorary doctorate.

909
00:43:20.848 --> 00:43:23.517
- [both chuckle]
- I fulfilled a promise to my father.

910
00:43:23.601 --> 00:43:24.727
Give me a break.

911
00:43:24.810 --> 00:43:26.770
Henry Kissinger who? Come on.

912
00:43:26.854 --> 00:43:27.855
King Pelé!

913
00:43:27.938 --> 00:43:29.565
That is… that's different.

914
00:43:29.648 --> 00:43:32.192
I couldn't contain myself
from asking him for an autograph.

915
00:43:32.276 --> 00:43:33.319
[both laugh]

916
00:43:33.402 --> 00:43:36.447
I imagine that Don Guillermo Cañedo
played a key role in all of this.

917
00:43:36.530 --> 00:43:38.824
You know. it's funny.
I thought so too but…

918
00:43:38.907 --> 00:43:40.451
And don't get me wrong. okay?

919
00:43:40.534 --> 00:43:43.746
I mean.
we can't keep living off past glories.

920
00:43:43.829 --> 00:43:46.248
The 1970 World Cup was over a decade ago.

921
00:43:46.332 --> 00:43:48.917
At the end of the day. the president
of FEMEXFUT has to do it.

922
00:43:49.001 --> 00:43:51.879
has to take charge.
to step in and set the vision.

923
00:43:51.962 --> 00:43:53.922
- You understand?
- Yes.

924
00:43:54.006 --> 00:43:56.133
- [both chuckle]
- Yeah. That's life. am I right?

925
00:43:56.216 --> 00:43:57.301
That's how it is.

926
00:43:57.384 --> 00:44:00.262
"We must forget the triumphs of the '60s"?

927
00:44:00.846 --> 00:44:03.474
[clicks tongue] So I'm an institution?

928
00:44:05.059 --> 00:44:08.562
You should've just said I have
to wear diapers to bed and call it a day.

929
00:44:08.646 --> 00:44:09.813
Would've been easier.

930
00:44:13.108 --> 00:44:14.693
Come on. Guillermo.

931
00:44:15.402 --> 00:44:17.112
You know the drill.

932
00:44:17.196 --> 00:44:19.281
That's just how the media is.

933
00:44:19.365 --> 00:44:23.077
Especially that reporter.
Watch out for her. Some woman named Tania.

934
00:44:23.160 --> 00:44:25.746
So you've turned Kissinger against you.

935
00:44:25.829 --> 00:44:27.498
And Steve Ross's daughter.

936
00:44:28.123 --> 00:44:30.084
Why add names to the list?

937
00:44:31.627 --> 00:44:32.753
You're right. [sighs]

938
00:44:32.836 --> 00:44:33.921
It's a shame.

939
00:44:35.005 --> 00:44:37.966
I'll be more careful next time
so I'm not taken out of context.

940
00:44:39.385 --> 00:44:42.429
I've made a decision. We're going
with the technical team from Puma.

941
00:44:43.013 --> 00:44:44.807
The América's current champion.

942
00:44:44.890 --> 00:44:46.600
I know that. I know that.

943
00:44:46.684 --> 00:44:49.103
But we want to make Hugo happy.

944
00:44:49.186 --> 00:44:51.480
That's why we're going
with the coach they had in Mexico.

945
00:44:51.563 --> 00:44:54.108
You know that's really gonna piss off
the owner of América.

946
00:44:54.191 --> 00:44:56.610
Who. by the way. also owns the World Cup.

947
00:44:56.694 --> 00:44:58.779
Who. by the way.
also knows how things work.

948
00:44:58.862 --> 00:45:00.489
It's just business.

949
00:45:01.782 --> 00:45:03.367
I'll speak to Emilio. all right?

950
00:45:03.450 --> 00:45:05.577
I mean. stop stressing. Guillermo.

951
00:45:06.704 --> 00:45:08.205
[Guillermo sighs]

952
00:45:08.288 --> 00:45:10.290
[tense music rises]

953
00:45:25.597 --> 00:45:27.725
- [chuckles]
- [tense music fades]

954
00:45:27.808 --> 00:45:28.892
[whistle blows]

955
00:45:28.976 --> 00:45:32.479
If I accept. it'll be on <i>my </i>terms.

956
00:45:32.563 --> 00:45:34.606
Of course. Whatever you say.

957
00:45:35.482 --> 00:45:39.027
I'm gonna need every single player
to go to training camp.

958
00:45:39.111 --> 00:45:41.196
Mm-hmm. Well. right. Same as always.

959
00:45:41.280 --> 00:45:42.656
For one year.

960
00:45:43.240 --> 00:45:46.243
One year? You can't be serious. What?

961
00:45:46.326 --> 00:45:47.745
For a… what do you mean?

962
00:45:47.828 --> 00:45:49.538
Are you pulling my leg. or what?

963
00:45:50.914 --> 00:45:52.833
And what am I supposed
to do with the league. man?

964
00:45:52.916 --> 00:45:56.086
You're telling me you wanna take
the best players for a whole year?

965
00:45:56.170 --> 00:45:58.505
And what? I'll play with reserves?
Are you kidding?

966
00:45:58.589 --> 00:46:01.759
I'll coach the national team.
You do your job.

967
00:46:03.218 --> 00:46:05.179
All right. Let's go. Come on.

968
00:46:07.347 --> 00:46:08.432
Let's go. boys!

969
00:46:08.515 --> 00:46:10.100
You've really got some nerve. buddy.

970
00:46:10.184 --> 00:46:13.187
Asking me. Hugo Sánchez.
to give up captaincy. don't you agree?

971
00:46:13.270 --> 00:46:16.732
You know that I can't just impose
a captain on Bora.

972
00:46:16.815 --> 00:46:19.651
But you know damn well everyone
in this country knows who our leader is.

973
00:46:19.735 --> 00:46:22.070
So. why don't you give me
that title. then?

974
00:46:22.154 --> 00:46:24.531
Maradona is the captain of Argentina.

975
00:46:24.615 --> 00:46:28.660
Platini's the captain of France.
Who should our captain be here?

976
00:46:28.744 --> 00:46:30.662
Do I have to spell it out for you?

977
00:46:31.455 --> 00:46:33.373
Now. if it can't be done.
it can't be done.

978
00:46:34.082 --> 00:46:36.668
We can take our time
and wait for Italy 1990 instead.

979
00:46:37.586 --> 00:46:38.712
[sighs]

980
00:46:40.881 --> 00:46:42.007
Listen. Hugo.

981
00:46:42.716 --> 00:46:46.512
Do you know what I would give
to wear your number out on that field?

982
00:46:47.137 --> 00:46:48.722
To have scored your goals?

983
00:46:49.932 --> 00:46:52.434
To break your records. to have your money?

984
00:46:57.314 --> 00:46:58.899
You got a gift from God.

985
00:47:00.234 --> 00:47:01.944
You've got magic.

986
00:47:02.528 --> 00:47:03.821
So why not share it?

987
00:47:05.113 --> 00:47:07.199
Give your country some joy. Hugo.

988
00:47:10.118 --> 00:47:13.914
You think you're gonna convince
me with all that fortune cookie nonsense?

989
00:47:14.456 --> 00:47:15.707
[scoffs]

990
00:47:16.583 --> 00:47:17.960
It was worth a shot.

991
00:47:21.880 --> 00:47:23.423
All right. [clears throat]

992
00:47:24.007 --> 00:47:25.259
Alright. Hugo.

993
00:47:26.385 --> 00:47:27.469
What'll it take?

994
00:47:27.970 --> 00:47:29.012
The standard stuff.

995
00:47:29.096 --> 00:47:30.639
You know. not much.

996
00:47:31.431 --> 00:47:33.851
I can't be exclusive
with team brands alone.

997
00:47:34.518 --> 00:47:36.144
I have prior commitments.

998
00:47:36.228 --> 00:47:37.896
And with this demanding
training schedule.

999
00:47:37.980 --> 00:47:41.733
plus the friendly matches
they're making us play…

1000
00:47:41.817 --> 00:47:43.944
It's simply too much to handle.

1001
00:47:48.699 --> 00:47:50.909
All right. look.
I'm gonna make you an offer.

1002
00:47:50.993 --> 00:47:52.870
Now. this stays between us. okay?

1003
00:47:53.954 --> 00:47:56.874
Knock yourself out.
Do as many commercials as you want.

1004
00:47:56.957 --> 00:47:59.751
Have as many commitments as you want.

1005
00:47:59.835 --> 00:48:04.506
In exchange. your campaign for captaincy
will be shelved indefinitely.

1006
00:48:05.507 --> 00:48:07.092
[energetic music playing]

1007
00:48:07.175 --> 00:48:09.553
[Matrín] <i>Hugo made a fortune</i>
<i>with his commercials.</i>

1008
00:48:09.636 --> 00:48:13.056
<i>Pichichi knew exactly what he was doing.</i>
<i>And he wasn't the only one.</i>

1009
00:48:13.140 --> 00:48:16.059
<i>From the stadium renovations alone.</i>
<i>the contract allocations.</i>

1010
00:48:16.143 --> 00:48:17.978
<i>and sponsorship deals.</i>

1011
00:48:18.061 --> 00:48:20.814
<i>massive amounts of money</i>
<i>started flowing through FEMEXFUT.</i>

1012
00:48:20.898 --> 00:48:23.817
<i>And there I was.</i>
<i>right at the center of it all.</i>

1013
00:48:23.901 --> 00:48:25.861
<i>Azcárraga on one side.</i>

1014
00:48:25.944 --> 00:48:28.572
<i>the politician overseeing</i>
<i>the World Cup budget on the other.</i>

1015
00:48:28.655 --> 00:48:30.949
<i>"El Tigre" opened his home to me.</i>

1016
00:48:31.033 --> 00:48:33.535
<i>and the cherry on top of the cake</i>
<i>was having Susana by my side.</i>

1017
00:48:33.619 --> 00:48:38.165
So. I'm there. and suddenly the bastard
shows up with his little red suit

1018
00:48:38.248 --> 00:48:40.042
and his hammer in tow.

1019
00:48:40.125 --> 00:48:42.794
- [all laugh]
- Really?

1020
00:48:42.878 --> 00:48:45.380
[Azcárraga] I wanted to kill him!

1021
00:48:45.464 --> 00:48:47.466
And just look how far he's come.

1022
00:48:47.549 --> 00:48:51.011
Making more money than Pimstein.
More than Ernesto.

1023
00:48:51.094 --> 00:48:55.557
Emilio. why don't you use Chapulín?
He could be in all of your commercials.

1024
00:48:55.641 --> 00:48:59.478
Seriously! He could rile the crowd
in the stadium. do sets in Querétaro.

1025
00:48:59.561 --> 00:49:01.438
Yeah. yeah. yeah. Martín. hire him.

1026
00:49:01.521 --> 00:49:03.482
Sure we just build his salary
into the bid.

1027
00:49:03.565 --> 00:49:06.735
- Works for everyone. It's a win-win.right?
- [politician] How's that coming along?

1028
00:49:06.818 --> 00:49:09.321
Coming along great.
All we need now is the vendor.

1029
00:49:09.404 --> 00:49:12.115
The bid folder's ready to go.
and it has FEMEXFUT's seal on it.

1030
00:49:15.410 --> 00:49:18.497
What did I say? I told you he's one of us.

1031
00:49:18.580 --> 00:49:19.539
- Memo!
- [Cañedo] Huh?

1032
00:49:19.623 --> 00:49:21.291
You doubted me. right? Didn't you?

1033
00:49:21.375 --> 00:49:24.252
Well. it's not like you made it easy
for me with this kid.

1034
00:49:24.336 --> 00:49:26.338
[Martín] Damn. Guillermo.
Don't do me like that.

1035
00:49:26.421 --> 00:49:27.798
[Cañedo] I'm just messing with you.

1036
00:49:27.881 --> 00:49:29.758
Wait a second. Don't I know you?

1037
00:49:32.052 --> 00:49:33.053
That's right.

1038
00:49:33.845 --> 00:49:35.472
Uh. from where? Remind me.

1039
00:49:36.848 --> 00:49:38.475
Uh. Acapulco.

1040
00:49:38.558 --> 00:49:41.186
Right. from Paco Quintanilla's house.

1041
00:49:41.269 --> 00:49:42.646
Are you his wife?

1042
00:49:42.729 --> 00:49:44.940
- [tense. comical music playing]
- I <i>was</i>.

1043
00:49:45.023 --> 00:49:47.526
Oh. darling! I know who you are.

1044
00:49:48.026 --> 00:49:51.571
She was with us at the New Year's party.
the one in Los Angeles.

1045
00:49:51.655 --> 00:49:53.991
That's the one. What a party. Paula. Yes.

1046
00:49:54.074 --> 00:49:55.534
Do you know Paco?

1047
00:49:55.617 --> 00:49:58.412
- [Martín] No. No.
- He's the best. What's he doing now?

1048
00:49:58.495 --> 00:49:59.746
He treated you like a queen.

1049
00:49:59.830 --> 00:50:02.416
Oh. Martín. you should've seen
his house in Acapulco.

1050
00:50:02.499 --> 00:50:04.584
A spectacular house.
overlooking the beach.

1051
00:50:04.668 --> 00:50:07.045
- It was nice.
- [Azcárraga] Something out of a magazine.

1052
00:50:07.129 --> 00:50:09.172
Huge house.
Hey. this one here's expensive.

1053
00:50:09.256 --> 00:50:12.259
Oh no. You've got it wrong.
<i>He's </i>the one costing <i>me </i>money.

1054
00:50:12.342 --> 00:50:13.719
He's expensive. right? [laughs]

1055
00:50:13.802 --> 00:50:17.556
Emilio. remember those wild parties
that he would throw at that house?

1056
00:50:17.639 --> 00:50:20.225
- [Azcárraga] Of course I do.
- You hired that musician.

1057
00:50:20.308 --> 00:50:21.518
- His name?
- Barry Manilow.

1058
00:50:21.601 --> 00:50:22.978
- Remember?
- [Azcárraga] Uh-huh.

1059
00:50:23.061 --> 00:50:23.937
That was crazy.

1060
00:50:24.021 --> 00:50:26.857
Once a girl gets treated like a princess.
they're always a princess.

1061
00:50:26.940 --> 00:50:28.400
Watch out. man. Look at me.

1062
00:50:28.483 --> 00:50:31.278
With my Verito.
everything served on a silver platter.

1063
00:50:31.361 --> 00:50:33.822
I don't know. Vero.
Personally. I love silver platters.

1064
00:50:33.905 --> 00:50:36.324
It's all those <i>pricks </i>I can do without.

1065
00:50:37.034 --> 00:50:38.660
[awkward silence]

1066
00:50:38.744 --> 00:50:39.995
[exhales]

1067
00:50:41.038 --> 00:50:44.332
[chuckles] All right. then.
Enough gossip for one night.

1068
00:50:44.416 --> 00:50:49.421
[sniffles] Gentlemen. let's chat.
Excuse us. ladies. Come on. [sighs]

1069
00:50:50.005 --> 00:50:51.048
[Martín clears throat]

1070
00:50:52.340 --> 00:50:53.633
[sighs]

1071
00:50:55.135 --> 00:50:56.762
Tell me something. darling.

1072
00:50:56.845 --> 00:51:00.640
- Who got the house in the divorce?
- Paco. Paco got the house.

1073
00:51:00.724 --> 00:51:03.977
No. I've got the best lawyer. honey.
Just ask.

1074
00:51:04.061 --> 00:51:07.314
- Hey. I'm sorry. I had to say something.
- Hey. no. no. no.

1075
00:51:07.397 --> 00:51:09.858
No. you don't apologize.
That guy's a fucking asshole.

1076
00:51:09.941 --> 00:51:11.735
I mean. if you had any idea what Paco--

1077
00:51:11.818 --> 00:51:14.571
- No. no. It's okay. Don't worry.
- [woman] Drive safe.

1078
00:51:14.654 --> 00:51:17.991
- Oh no! You're leaving already?
- Yeah. we are. Thanks so much.

1079
00:51:18.075 --> 00:51:20.327
- So nice to see you.
- What a great dinner. Delicious.

1080
00:51:20.410 --> 00:51:22.412
You are not leaving
without giving me your number.

1081
00:51:22.496 --> 00:51:23.538
<i>Emilio. thanks so much.</i>

1082
00:51:23.622 --> 00:51:27.751
[Martín] <i>Honestly. despite the hiccups.</i>
<i>everything was going great.</i>

1083
00:51:27.834 --> 00:51:31.838
<i>Then just nine months</i>
<i>before the World Cup. it happened.</i>

1084
00:51:34.257 --> 00:51:37.094
[reporter] <i>September 19. 1985.</i>

1085
00:51:38.178 --> 00:51:42.808
<i>The earthquake registered a magnitude</i>
<i>of 8.6 on the Richter scale.</i>

1086
00:51:42.891 --> 00:51:47.229
<i>The tremor struck</i>
<i>at approximately 7:19 in the morning.</i>

1087
00:51:47.312 --> 00:51:51.858
<i>The epicenter has been identified</i>
<i>at 16.5 degrees north.</i>

1088
00:51:51.942 --> 00:51:54.778
<i>and 10.3 degrees west.</i>

1089
00:51:54.861 --> 00:51:57.364
[Havelange] <i>Mexico's pain</i>
<i>is FIFA's pain. Martín.</i>

1090
00:51:57.447 --> 00:52:00.700
<i>We want you to know.</i>
<i>we stand with you. Always.</i>

1091
00:52:00.784 --> 00:52:02.786
Oh. thank you so much. João.

1092
00:52:02.869 --> 00:52:05.539
Your words are truly appreciated.
Thank you.

1093
00:52:05.622 --> 00:52:07.165
<i>And because we care about you.</i>

1094
00:52:07.249 --> 00:52:10.335
<i>we want you to focus</i>
<i>on what matters most right now.</i>

1095
00:52:10.418 --> 00:52:12.420
Yeah. and we're on it. João.
That's what we're doing.

1096
00:52:12.504 --> 00:52:15.132
<i>We really think you should devote</i>
<i>all of your resources</i>

1097
00:52:15.215 --> 00:52:16.508
<i>and energy to your people.</i>

1098
00:52:16.591 --> 00:52:20.095
João. you're not taking
the World Cup from us. are you?

1099
00:52:21.721 --> 00:52:25.267
The worst thing they could do right now
is take the Cup from us.

1100
00:52:26.268 --> 00:52:28.937
Honey. everyone is terrified right now.

1101
00:52:30.605 --> 00:52:32.274
Let things settle down a bit.

1102
00:52:32.357 --> 00:52:34.901
and then you'll be able
to handle everything more calmly.

1103
00:52:34.985 --> 00:52:39.030
This country needs a good fucking reason
to get back on its feet. And this is it!

1104
00:52:39.114 --> 00:52:40.240
This is it.

1105
00:52:41.199 --> 00:52:42.367
[sighs]

1106
00:52:42.450 --> 00:52:45.912
I need a game plan on
how to tell Emilio. I'll only have five--

1107
00:52:45.996 --> 00:52:48.248
[reporter speaking indistinctly on TV]

1108
00:52:53.003 --> 00:52:55.714
Hey. [sighs]

1109
00:52:55.797 --> 00:52:57.257
I'm sorry. baby.

1110
00:53:02.095 --> 00:53:03.805
I'm just not thinking right.

1111
00:53:07.225 --> 00:53:08.310
[softly] Come here.

1112
00:53:09.019 --> 00:53:10.478
[sighs]

1113
00:53:10.562 --> 00:53:11.771
[Martín sniffles]

1114
00:53:13.690 --> 00:53:14.941
[exhales]

1115
00:53:23.700 --> 00:53:25.160
I'm just gonna…

1116
00:53:25.243 --> 00:53:28.705
I'm gonna call Mayrita real quick
to set up a meeting with Emilio.

1117
00:53:30.290 --> 00:53:31.833
It'll be quick. okay?

1118
00:53:37.672 --> 00:53:42.010
Put Mayrita on the phone.
Mr. De la Torre. her boss. Put her on.

1119
00:53:42.677 --> 00:53:44.638
What do you mean. she didn't go to work?

1120
00:53:44.721 --> 00:53:47.766
[inhales sharply] Yeah. well.
we all have emergencies. okay?

1121
00:53:47.849 --> 00:53:50.060
It's an earthquake.
but we also just can't ditch work.

1122
00:53:51.728 --> 00:53:55.649
Then find me someone who can get me
in touch with Mr. Azcárraga. please.

1123
00:53:56.775 --> 00:53:58.151
Well. find him!

1124
00:53:58.235 --> 00:53:59.319
It's not official yet.

1125
00:53:59.402 --> 00:54:01.905
but they're considering
taking it to Germany.

1126
00:54:01.988 --> 00:54:03.531
On top of that. the Italians

1127
00:54:03.615 --> 00:54:05.742
and the French
have already raised their hands.

1128
00:54:05.825 --> 00:54:08.161
Of fuck. we gotta speed up
those inspection reports

1129
00:54:08.245 --> 00:54:11.122
so we can prove that the stadium
didn't suffer any structural damage.

1130
00:54:11.206 --> 00:54:14.960
And we gotta keep repair costs
to a minimum to avoid drawing attention.

1131
00:54:15.043 --> 00:54:18.755
Jesus Christ. are you serious?
You're worried about the stadiums?

1132
00:54:18.838 --> 00:54:21.299
While you sip
on your stupid little coffee!

1133
00:54:21.383 --> 00:54:24.302
God knows how many people
are under the rubble in Chapultepec.

1134
00:54:24.386 --> 00:54:25.679
<i>My </i>people!

1135
00:54:30.558 --> 00:54:31.935
[Azcárraga inhales sharply]

1136
00:54:34.479 --> 00:54:35.563
[Martín sighs]

1137
00:54:39.234 --> 00:54:41.528
I know this is a national tragedy.
Don Emilio.

1138
00:54:41.611 --> 00:54:43.405
It truly is horrific. It is.

1139
00:54:43.488 --> 00:54:45.949
And I know it's hit you
and the company very hard.

1140
00:54:48.285 --> 00:54:49.744
I don't want to be insensitive.

1141
00:54:49.828 --> 00:54:52.038
but someone needs
to think about the future.

1142
00:54:52.122 --> 00:54:55.250
The country is mourning.
What happens tomorrow matters.

1143
00:54:55.333 --> 00:54:56.918
We'll need something to hold on to.

1144
00:54:57.002 --> 00:55:00.130
I know that football
isn't saving any lives. okay?

1145
00:55:00.213 --> 00:55:03.800
Twenty-two dumbasses
chasing a ball around a pitch all day.

1146
00:55:03.883 --> 00:55:08.054
But very few things…
give us that level of joy.

1147
00:55:08.138 --> 00:55:10.932
- That moment of real inspiration.
- [quietly] Yeah.

1148
00:55:11.016 --> 00:55:13.226
When the underdog
believes he just might win.

1149
00:55:13.310 --> 00:55:16.146
Come on. Don Emilio. That's fucking gold!

1150
00:55:17.981 --> 00:55:21.109
But who am I to say that?
You know better than anyone else.

1151
00:55:27.574 --> 00:55:28.950
What are you thinking?

1152
00:55:30.201 --> 00:55:32.704
If Guillermo can bring his pal.
Havelange. to Mexico.

1153
00:55:32.787 --> 00:55:34.998
I'll make sure he doesn't snatch
the World Cup from us.

1154
00:55:35.081 --> 00:55:36.416
You can trust me with this. sir.

1155
00:55:36.499 --> 00:55:38.251
And <i>can </i>we trust you?

1156
00:55:40.003 --> 00:55:43.965
[scoffs] Well. of course.
Of course you can trust me.

1157
00:55:44.049 --> 00:55:47.427
If FIFA comes.
you'll have to keep your focus.

1158
00:55:48.303 --> 00:55:51.181
And what makes you think I'd lose focus?

1159
00:55:51.264 --> 00:55:54.184
Some matters are best settled
without women.

1160
00:55:55.226 --> 00:55:57.979
[Azcárraga] Your girlfriend's attitude
nearly screwed things up

1161
00:55:58.063 --> 00:55:59.731
with Secretary Valenzuela.

1162
00:55:59.814 --> 00:56:02.484
Uh. yes. I owe you both an apology.

1163
00:56:03.401 --> 00:56:07.405
I'm so damn embarrassed.
And at your house. Don Emilio.

1164
00:56:07.489 --> 00:56:08.656
You… [sighs]

1165
00:56:09.532 --> 00:56:12.744
You know. once we left.
I ended the damn relationship. It's over.

1166
00:56:12.827 --> 00:56:17.290
I've already had issues with her.
I don't know what got into me.

1167
00:56:17.791 --> 00:56:18.875
Yes. I do.

1168
00:56:18.958 --> 00:56:20.543
It was the mini skirts.

1169
00:56:21.586 --> 00:56:24.255
The mini skirts. But it's over now.

1170
00:56:24.339 --> 00:56:26.132
I'm laser focused.

1171
00:56:28.426 --> 00:56:30.345
Memo. can you get in touch with Havelange?

1172
00:56:30.428 --> 00:56:32.389
I got it. Don't worry about it.

1173
00:56:32.472 --> 00:56:34.224
Don't fuck this up. Martín.

1174
00:56:35.308 --> 00:56:37.936
[Martín] <i>When you're talking</i>
<i>to the most powerful man in Mexico.</i>

1175
00:56:38.019 --> 00:56:39.771
<i>you tell him what he wants to hear.</i>

1176
00:56:39.854 --> 00:56:42.065
<i>I needed to focus on Hermann Neuberger.</i>

1177
00:56:42.148 --> 00:56:43.274
<i>the FIFA </i>official sent

1178
00:56:43.358 --> 00:56:46.277
<i>to decide if they were taking</i>
<i>the World Cup away from us.</i>

1179
00:56:48.488 --> 00:56:49.948
Welcome to FEMEXFUT. sir.

1180
00:56:50.031 --> 00:56:51.408
How was your flight?

1181
00:56:51.491 --> 00:56:53.535
[sighs] It was long.

1182
00:56:55.412 --> 00:56:57.455
How bout we drink some coffee. huh?

1183
00:56:57.539 --> 00:56:59.207
Would you like a coffee? Coffee?

1184
00:56:59.290 --> 00:57:02.502
This is traditional Mexican art. Talavera.

1185
00:57:02.585 --> 00:57:05.255
[Neuberger] <i>The FIFA committee</i>
<i>has reviewed this thoroughly.</i>

1186
00:57:05.338 --> 00:57:09.008
and we are deeply sorry
about the tragedy that's unfolded.

1187
00:57:09.092 --> 00:57:10.301
[inhales sharply]

1188
00:57:10.385 --> 00:57:13.638
But I'm afraid
the World Cup cannot stay here.

1189
00:57:13.721 --> 00:57:17.142
[Martín] <i>Turns out two days before.</i>
<i>there had been a meeting in Switzerland.</i>

1190
00:57:17.225 --> 00:57:18.726
{\an8}[Jackie] Look at this tragedy.

1191
00:57:18.810 --> 00:57:21.646
{\an8}FIFA needs to relocate
the tournament somewhere safe.

1192
00:57:21.729 --> 00:57:23.815
The US has the resources.

1193
00:57:23.898 --> 00:57:26.151
Anywhere else could mean
not having the Cup in '86.

1194
00:57:26.943 --> 00:57:28.403
[Martín] <i>And you know what?</i>

1195
00:57:28.486 --> 00:57:31.030
<i>I would have done</i>
<i>the same thing that gringa did.</i>

1196
00:57:31.114 --> 00:57:32.824
Since you came all this way.

1197
00:57:32.907 --> 00:57:35.034
we'd like to show you
around the city a little.

1198
00:57:35.952 --> 00:57:36.953
Shall we?

1199
00:57:37.829 --> 00:57:40.582
I know that right now
the whole world is talking

1200
00:57:40.665 --> 00:57:43.668
about how this city has collapsed.

1201
00:57:43.751 --> 00:57:46.629
But listen.
there's something the newspapers

1202
00:57:46.713 --> 00:57:49.757
and the news on TV
don't want you to know. Hermann.

1203
00:57:49.841 --> 00:57:51.426
That's what we want to show you.

1204
00:57:52.093 --> 00:57:55.013
- [man 1] Come on. come on!
- Go. go. Mike. Go ahead.

1205
00:57:55.096 --> 00:57:56.389
[volunteers chattering]

1206
00:57:56.473 --> 00:57:57.640
[Martín sniffles]

1207
00:57:57.724 --> 00:58:01.060
[jackhammer whirring]

1208
00:58:01.144 --> 00:58:02.896
It's tough seeing the damage.

1209
00:58:03.605 --> 00:58:05.064
Not easy to see this.

1210
00:58:05.148 --> 00:58:06.483
[man 2] Hey. Carlos!

1211
00:58:06.983 --> 00:58:09.986
- See. those right there?
- [man 2] Watch out for the pillar!

1212
00:58:10.069 --> 00:58:11.863
They're not state officials.

1213
00:58:11.946 --> 00:58:15.283
They're civilians helping other civilians.

1214
00:58:15.366 --> 00:58:18.203
I brought you because if you didn't see.
you wouldn't believe it.

1215
00:58:18.286 --> 00:58:19.537
Take a look.

1216
00:58:20.038 --> 00:58:22.457
We'd like to show you the stadium.

1217
00:58:22.540 --> 00:58:25.084
- [engine starts]
- Just around the corner. Twenty minutes.

1218
00:58:27.003 --> 00:58:29.005
[energetic music playing]

1219
00:58:31.174 --> 00:58:32.509
[Martín] It was 20 minutes away

1220
00:58:32.592 --> 00:58:34.344
<i>because we had asked</i>
<i>President De la Madrid</i>

1221
00:58:34.427 --> 00:58:36.679
<i>to shut down the entire avenue for us.</i>

1222
00:58:36.763 --> 00:58:39.724
<i>We even got them to patch up</i>
<i>every damn pothole on the highway.</i>

1223
00:58:42.644 --> 00:58:45.021
[Martín] Great. Let's go. This way.

1224
00:58:45.104 --> 00:58:46.397
[grunts] Follow me.

1225
00:58:49.234 --> 00:58:51.402
Stadium Neza. '86.

1226
00:58:51.486 --> 00:58:54.239
Intact. sir. And remodeled
for our World Cup. Come this way.

1227
00:58:54.322 --> 00:58:57.158
[Martín] <i>The truth is.</i>
<i>the stadium only got a light touch-up.</i>

1228
00:58:57.242 --> 00:59:00.453
<i>But 20.000 food packages</i>
<i>and a whole load of fun</i>

1229
00:59:00.537 --> 00:59:02.997
<i>were enough to fill that place</i>
<i>with a staged crowd.</i>

1230
00:59:03.081 --> 00:59:04.499
- [laughs]
- [crowd chanting]

1231
00:59:04.582 --> 00:59:08.878
- What do you think? Hey. give me that.
- [crowd] Hermann! Hermann!

1232
00:59:08.962 --> 00:59:10.046
After you.

1233
00:59:10.129 --> 00:59:12.799
[Martín] Hermann! [laughs]

1234
00:59:12.882 --> 00:59:14.509
Thank you for being here.

1235
00:59:14.592 --> 00:59:18.179
I appreciate you.
Do you want to speak first. Hermann?

1236
00:59:18.263 --> 00:59:19.722
- Yes.
- Don't be shy. Go ahead.

1237
00:59:19.806 --> 00:59:22.392
- Yeah. Please.
- Tell them why there's no Cup in Mexico.

1238
00:59:23.560 --> 00:59:24.894
I'm kidding.

1239
00:59:24.978 --> 00:59:25.937
[both laugh]

1240
00:59:26.020 --> 00:59:27.146
- Come on.
- It's a joke.

1241
00:59:27.230 --> 00:59:30.191
We're messing with you.
Today we party. okay? No talking.

1242
00:59:30.275 --> 00:59:31.484
[chuckling]

1243
00:59:31.568 --> 00:59:33.486
Relax. Enjoy.

1244
00:59:33.570 --> 00:59:35.446
[Martín] Hm. [sniffles]

1245
00:59:35.530 --> 00:59:37.782
- [clears throat]
- [feedback squeals]

1246
00:59:39.284 --> 00:59:40.618
Good morning.

1247
00:59:41.452 --> 00:59:44.372
We appreciate you all
for being here today.

1248
00:59:45.164 --> 00:59:49.460
I'd like to begin
by saying that if I'm standing here now.

1249
00:59:49.544 --> 00:59:52.338
it's simply because.
like you. I was lucky.

1250
00:59:52.422 --> 00:59:54.966
Lucky in a way my neighbors were not.

1251
00:59:55.842 --> 00:59:58.970
And all those days and endless nights

1252
00:59:59.053 --> 01:00:00.805
that I'm sure. like you.

1253
01:00:01.556 --> 01:00:06.561
I spent clearing rubble.
searching for bodies.

1254
01:00:06.644 --> 01:00:10.148
I started thinking.
"I have a responsibility."

1255
01:00:11.274 --> 01:00:13.693
A responsibility to give our country hope.

1256
01:00:13.776 --> 01:00:17.280
The World Cup needs to stay
right here in Mexico!

1257
01:00:17.363 --> 01:00:20.575
[crowd cheers]

1258
01:00:20.658 --> 01:00:22.785
So. Mr. Neuberger…

1259
01:00:22.869 --> 01:00:26.956
I'm sure it's clear by now that
this stadium is in pristine condition.

1260
01:00:27.540 --> 01:00:29.083
But that's not the point.

1261
01:00:29.167 --> 01:00:31.127
The point is all of you here.

1262
01:00:31.210 --> 01:00:34.255
It's the people
who have gathered here today

1263
01:00:34.339 --> 01:00:38.676
of their own volition
to remind us all that Mexico is ready

1264
01:00:38.760 --> 01:00:41.387
to welcome the whole world.
to celebrate together!

1265
01:00:41.471 --> 01:00:42.889
How's that sound?

1266
01:00:43.640 --> 01:00:47.310
Yes. Mr. Neuberger.
the impact was profound.

1267
01:00:47.393 --> 01:00:49.187
But it did not break us.

1268
01:00:49.270 --> 01:00:51.272
And that is why now. more than ever.

1269
01:00:51.356 --> 01:00:54.359
our nation deserves
to deliver and celebrate

1270
01:00:54.442 --> 01:00:57.320
the most amazing World Cup in history!

1271
01:00:57.403 --> 01:00:59.322
Welcome to México. Hermann!

1272
01:00:59.405 --> 01:01:01.699
[mariachi tune playing]

1273
01:01:14.128 --> 01:01:15.129
This is Mexico!

1274
01:01:15.213 --> 01:01:17.048
It's smooth. Don't worry.

1275
01:01:17.548 --> 01:01:18.966
Come on. Come on.

1276
01:01:22.011 --> 01:01:24.305
- [all laugh]
- "I don't drink tequila."

1277
01:01:24.389 --> 01:01:26.766
- Well. you do here!
- Chug. chug! Oh my God!

1278
01:01:29.102 --> 01:01:30.520
It's football. baby!

1279
01:01:32.730 --> 01:01:34.482
[shouts]

1280
01:01:34.565 --> 01:01:35.692
[grunts]

1281
01:01:35.775 --> 01:01:37.026
- Yahoo!
- [crowd cheers]

1282
01:01:37.819 --> 01:01:38.695
[grunts]

1283
01:01:39.737 --> 01:01:40.571
[crowd cheers]

1284
01:01:40.655 --> 01:01:42.115
Goal. motherfucker! Goal!

1285
01:01:42.198 --> 01:01:43.491
[groans]

1286
01:01:44.659 --> 01:01:45.618
[group laughs]

1287
01:01:45.702 --> 01:01:47.120
- Other bottle?
- I got something to say.

1288
01:01:47.203 --> 01:01:49.330
- No. no. no. no.
- Viva Mexico!

1289
01:01:49.414 --> 01:01:52.417
Hey. Hermann. Here's a little something.

1290
01:01:52.500 --> 01:01:53.960
Might help with your decision.

1291
01:01:54.043 --> 01:01:55.378
[in German] Thank you.

1292
01:01:55.461 --> 01:01:58.256
- Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.
- [laughs]

1293
01:01:58.339 --> 01:01:59.674
[Martín chuckles] This guy!

1294
01:01:59.757 --> 01:02:03.302
See. this is what I meant
when I said you need to focus.

1295
01:02:03.928 --> 01:02:05.346
Yeah. I hear you.

1296
01:02:05.430 --> 01:02:09.100
Um. the problem isn't women. Martín.

1297
01:02:09.726 --> 01:02:12.895
Look at me. If there's one thing
I'm fuckin' crazy about. it's women.

1298
01:02:12.979 --> 01:02:14.147
[both chuckle]

1299
01:02:14.230 --> 01:02:17.567
But that doesn't mean I'm gonna allow them
to walk all over me.

1300
01:02:17.650 --> 01:02:20.486
And it's not as hard
as you might think it is.

1301
01:02:20.570 --> 01:02:23.990
Martín. once I reached
a certain point in my life.

1302
01:02:24.073 --> 01:02:26.826
I knew I had to get organized. okay?

1303
01:02:26.909 --> 01:02:28.828
That's all I had to do.

1304
01:02:28.911 --> 01:02:30.663
Now. if you're hopelessly in love…

1305
01:02:30.747 --> 01:02:31.789
[Martín chuckles]

1306
01:02:31.873 --> 01:02:34.792
…well. then maybe
we can help you get over it. yeah?

1307
01:02:34.876 --> 01:02:37.545
Okay wait a minute.
You've lost me. Emilio.

1308
01:02:37.628 --> 01:02:39.255
- What are you saying?
- Listen.

1309
01:02:39.338 --> 01:02:41.174
Between now and the World Cup.

1310
01:02:41.257 --> 01:02:43.176
you're gonna get lots of visibility.

1311
01:02:43.259 --> 01:02:45.261
lots of events.
cameras on you all the time.

1312
01:02:45.344 --> 01:02:46.387
Hm. [chuckles]

1313
01:02:46.471 --> 01:02:49.348
You can't even hide the excitement
behind your eyes.

1314
01:02:50.099 --> 01:02:53.352
My advice is to get a girl
who knows how to stand next to you.

1315
01:02:53.436 --> 01:02:58.566
Okay? Someone high-profile.
like… like Lucía. for example.

1316
01:02:59.859 --> 01:03:01.611
[chuckles] What? The redhead?

1317
01:03:01.694 --> 01:03:05.531
[both laugh]

1318
01:03:05.615 --> 01:03:08.659
- No fuckin' way. No. no. no. no. no.
- No?

1319
01:03:08.743 --> 01:03:10.286
I'm not as cool as you. Emilio.

1320
01:03:10.369 --> 01:03:13.206
I can't do both at once. you know?
I'll end up losing focus.

1321
01:03:13.289 --> 01:03:14.999
Well. it's your loss. then. Your loss.

1322
01:03:15.082 --> 01:03:16.542
[scoffs] I don't know.

1323
01:03:16.626 --> 01:03:18.753
Maybe I'll accept your offer
after the inauguration.

1324
01:03:18.836 --> 01:03:22.173
Hm. Are you still in touch with your ex?

1325
01:03:24.967 --> 01:03:26.177
- No.
- No?

1326
01:03:26.260 --> 01:03:27.345
Why do you ask?

1327
01:03:28.554 --> 01:03:30.765
Paula's obsessed
with that Acapulco house now.

1328
01:03:30.848 --> 01:03:33.976
The one that she shared
with that crooked shit. Paco Quintanilla.

1329
01:03:34.060 --> 01:03:35.561
[sighs] Don't tell me that.

1330
01:03:35.645 --> 01:03:38.815
- It's how it is.
- I broke it off. That's dead.

1331
01:03:38.898 --> 01:03:41.901
Well. you're better off
because that woman's not good for you.

1332
01:03:42.401 --> 01:03:44.237
Cheers to that. [sighs]

1333
01:03:44.320 --> 01:03:46.405
- Great job. kid.
- [Martín chuckles]

1334
01:03:46.489 --> 01:03:47.532
Well done.

1335
01:03:48.282 --> 01:03:49.534
[Martín sighs]

1336
01:03:51.786 --> 01:03:53.871
My love. [laughs]

1337
01:03:53.955 --> 01:03:56.582
Are you ready to attend
the opening ceremony

1338
01:03:56.666 --> 01:03:59.585
of the 1986 Mexico World Cup

1339
01:03:59.669 --> 01:04:01.879
in the presidential box?

1340
01:04:01.963 --> 01:04:03.464
- [laughs]
- So you really did it. huh?

1341
01:04:03.548 --> 01:04:06.050
[laughs] Mwah.

1342
01:04:06.133 --> 01:04:10.179
You should've seen him.
The poor bastard wants to be Mexican now.

1343
01:04:10.263 --> 01:04:12.932
[laughs] It was amazing.

1344
01:04:13.015 --> 01:04:15.434
Why didn't you take me with you?

1345
01:04:15.518 --> 01:04:17.770
Oh. it was just a bunch of…
a bunch of men. babe.

1346
01:04:17.854 --> 01:04:20.606
That kinda stuff's
like electing the pope. you know?

1347
01:04:20.690 --> 01:04:22.066
Pretty boring.

1348
01:04:22.149 --> 01:04:23.985
But you'll take me next time. won't you?

1349
01:04:24.068 --> 01:04:26.946
Or are you and I supposed
to be broken up by then?

1350
01:04:27.655 --> 01:04:28.698
Huh?

1351
01:04:28.781 --> 01:04:31.075
Well. see this morning.
I spoke to Paula Cussi.

1352
01:04:31.158 --> 01:04:32.577
who told me how sorry she was

1353
01:04:32.660 --> 01:04:34.996
to learn that you and I
are no longer together.

1354
01:04:35.830 --> 01:04:37.582
[chuckles]

1355
01:04:37.665 --> 01:04:40.251
No… Wait. no way. Seriously?

1356
01:04:41.669 --> 01:04:43.546
What a nutcase.

1357
01:04:43.629 --> 01:04:45.673
You're not gonna take her seriously.
are you?

1358
01:04:45.756 --> 01:04:49.093
You… you saw her at dinner.
She's a disaster.

1359
01:04:49.594 --> 01:04:51.304
But it's odd. isn't it?

1360
01:04:51.387 --> 01:04:53.014
[sighs] What is?

1361
01:04:53.097 --> 01:04:56.309
I don't know. that Azcárraga
would just lie about something like that.

1362
01:04:56.392 --> 01:04:57.977
It's really bizarre.

1363
01:04:58.060 --> 01:05:00.438
I don't know. I don't know. then.

1364
01:05:00.521 --> 01:05:03.983
I got the feeling
that he lies to everybody.

1365
01:05:04.066 --> 01:05:05.401
[sighs]

1366
01:05:05.484 --> 01:05:06.611
Martín.

1367
01:05:08.029 --> 01:05:09.739
Tell me the truth.

1368
01:05:10.781 --> 01:05:12.742
I <i>am </i>telling you the truth.

1369
01:05:16.954 --> 01:05:19.081
So. none of what I'm saying
happened at all?

1370
01:05:19.665 --> 01:05:21.834
I have no fucking clue
what you're talking about.

1371
01:05:21.918 --> 01:05:23.628
- [sniffles]
- Martín.

1372
01:05:23.711 --> 01:05:24.795
What?

1373
01:05:24.879 --> 01:05:26.172
Come on.

1374
01:05:26.255 --> 01:05:29.216
You're not lying to Azcárraga.
You're not lying to Paula Cussi.

1375
01:05:29.300 --> 01:05:31.385
It's <i>me </i>that you're lying to.

1376
01:05:31.469 --> 01:05:33.930
[scoffs] What do you want me to say. huh?

1377
01:05:35.097 --> 01:05:38.643
Fuck. how…
how could you not believe me. Susana?

1378
01:05:39.435 --> 01:05:41.646
It really fuckin' hurts. you know?

1379
01:05:41.729 --> 01:05:44.398
For fucks' sake. Are you serious?

1380
01:05:45.191 --> 01:05:47.109
What do you want from me? Huh?

1381
01:05:48.277 --> 01:05:49.737
What more do you want?

1382
01:05:51.030 --> 01:05:54.200
I don't know what your life was like
with Paco. that motherfucker.

1383
01:05:54.283 --> 01:05:56.744
But I am not him. honey. I'm different.

1384
01:05:56.827 --> 01:05:57.662
Damn. Martín.

1385
01:05:57.745 --> 01:05:59.956
It's almost impressive how you can do it.

1386
01:06:00.039 --> 01:06:02.124
Lying comes as natural
to you as breathing.

1387
01:06:02.208 --> 01:06:03.459
Oh. you're one to talk.

1388
01:06:03.542 --> 01:06:05.378
You're so honest. aren't you?

1389
01:06:05.461 --> 01:06:07.505
Why don't we talk about trust?

1390
01:06:07.588 --> 01:06:10.132
'Cause that's what it's about.
Trusting each other.

1391
01:06:11.133 --> 01:06:12.927
The wife of a… a criminal.

1392
01:06:13.010 --> 01:06:14.929
You were together
for four years. weren't you?

1393
01:06:15.012 --> 01:06:18.641
When were you gonna tell me. my love? Hmm?

1394
01:06:22.061 --> 01:06:23.229
Get out. Martín.

1395
01:06:25.356 --> 01:06:29.360
Okay. Fine…
You bet your ass I'm leaving. You got it.

1396
01:06:29.443 --> 01:06:32.530
Fuckin… I'm such a fucking idiot.

1397
01:06:33.698 --> 01:06:35.616
Sure. Sure. I'll leave.

1398
01:06:35.700 --> 01:06:37.618
You know. so you feel more comfortable.

1399
01:06:37.702 --> 01:06:39.161
I'll just…

1400
01:06:39.245 --> 01:06:41.330
Here's your fuckin' keys. right there!

1401
01:06:43.958 --> 01:06:45.292
[door slams]

1402
01:06:45.376 --> 01:06:47.878
["Frente a frente" by Jeanette playing]

1403
01:06:47.962 --> 01:06:51.173
[melancholic Spanish ballad continues]

1404
01:06:52.842 --> 01:06:54.593
[Martín] <i>I know.</i>

1405
01:06:54.677 --> 01:06:56.804
<i>What a fuckin' dumbass.</i>

1406
01:06:57.304 --> 01:06:59.348
<i>Susana was the best thing</i>
<i>that ever happened to me.</i>

1407
01:06:59.432 --> 01:07:03.811
<i>and I… I went.</i>
<i>and I screwed the whole thing up.</i>

1408
01:07:10.234 --> 01:07:11.444
[sighs]

1409
01:07:19.744 --> 01:07:21.912
[melancholic ballad swells]

1410
01:07:35.551 --> 01:07:39.597
[Martín] <i>That's how it was</i>
<i>until May 31. 1986.</i>

1411
01:07:40.598 --> 01:07:43.893
<i>the day more than 100.000 people</i>
<i>packed the Azteca Stadium.</i>

1412
01:07:43.976 --> 01:07:46.395
[crowd cheering]

1413
01:07:46.479 --> 01:07:48.022
[Martín] <i>Who would've thought?</i>

1414
01:07:48.105 --> 01:07:51.400
<i>All the work and sacrifice</i>
<i>I'd put in over the years…</i>

1415
01:07:51.484 --> 01:07:55.154
<i>The World Cup was off to a great start.</i>
<i>And there I was. brokenhearted.</i>

1416
01:07:55.946 --> 01:07:59.950
[José Ramón] <i>And the opening match</i>
<i>is underway. Mexico against Belgium!</i>

1417
01:08:00.034 --> 01:08:03.079
[announcer 1] <i>The ball swings</i>
<i>into the box and… Goal!</i>

1418
01:08:03.162 --> 01:08:07.708
<i>Quirarte. Fernando Quirarte scores</i>
<i>the first ball for the Mexican team.</i>

1419
01:08:07.792 --> 01:08:12.880
<i>To the middle left! Goal! By Hugo Sánchez.</i>

1420
01:08:12.963 --> 01:08:13.964
<i>Goal!</i>

1421
01:08:14.048 --> 01:08:16.592
[José Ramón] <i>Mexico's second match</i>
<i>against Paraguay.</i>

1422
01:08:16.675 --> 01:08:18.177
<i>Penalty for Mexico!</i>

1423
01:08:18.260 --> 01:08:19.762
[announcer 3] <i>Carrying the weight</i>

1424
01:08:19.845 --> 01:08:22.139
<i>of the whole team</i>
<i>on his shoulders. Hugo Sánchez!</i>

1425
01:08:22.223 --> 01:08:24.266
<i>Misses by an inch!</i>

1426
01:08:24.350 --> 01:08:27.770
[Martín] <i>All that talk about Real Madrid.</i>
<i>and he missed that penalty shot.</i>

1427
01:08:27.853 --> 01:08:29.271
HUGO MISSES!

1428
01:08:29.355 --> 01:08:31.941
<i>But still. we were just one step away</i>
<i>from the next round.</i>

1429
01:08:32.024 --> 01:08:34.110
<i>And everyone was happy.</i>

1430
01:08:34.902 --> 01:08:36.529
<i>Everyone except me.</i>

1431
01:08:40.366 --> 01:08:42.451
- I'm here to see her. thanks.
- [receptionist] Go ahead.

1432
01:08:43.619 --> 01:08:44.870
Yes. no problem. sir.

1433
01:08:44.954 --> 01:08:46.956
I'll have that quote
ready for you later today.

1434
01:08:47.039 --> 01:08:48.165
Of course. Yeah. Thanks.

1435
01:08:48.874 --> 01:08:50.334
[receiver clatters]

1436
01:08:50.417 --> 01:08:51.418
Hello there.

1437
01:08:52.378 --> 01:08:53.379
Hello.

1438
01:08:55.214 --> 01:08:57.758
May I…?
Just for a minute. I'll be super quick.

1439
01:08:57.842 --> 01:09:02.012
I have some information that might
be useful to your clients.

1440
01:09:03.764 --> 01:09:08.352
México's quarterfinal match…
will be in Monterrey.

1441
01:09:08.894 --> 01:09:11.605
Well. if we keep playing like this.
which I think we will.

1442
01:09:12.231 --> 01:09:17.945
In other words. a bunch of fans…
will decide to go to Monterrey overnight.

1443
01:09:19.155 --> 01:09:21.949
So basically. plane tickets.
travel packages.

1444
01:09:22.741 --> 01:09:25.703
The stadium fits 42.000.

1445
01:09:27.121 --> 01:09:28.289
Just a tip. [chuckles]

1446
01:09:28.372 --> 01:09:31.000
- Hm.
- Friend to friend. you know?

1447
01:09:31.625 --> 01:09:32.710
Thanks.

1448
01:09:34.170 --> 01:09:37.464
Thanks. Martín. Thanks for the… the info.

1449
01:09:40.259 --> 01:09:41.552
Well. so…

1450
01:09:42.636 --> 01:09:45.848
- I guess… Sorry. I got a call that--
- Susana…

1451
01:09:47.349 --> 01:09:49.602
Susana. I needed to see you again.

1452
01:09:53.564 --> 01:09:55.482
I really. really miss you.

1453
01:09:58.736 --> 01:10:00.821
[softly] What we had was so beautiful.

1454
01:10:03.073 --> 01:10:06.535
And I ruined it.
I know I ruined everything.

1455
01:10:08.704 --> 01:10:10.414
I was just overwhelmed.

1456
01:10:11.248 --> 01:10:13.042
I let my pride get the best of me.

1457
01:10:13.125 --> 01:10:14.668
I'm so sorry. Susana.

1458
01:10:15.419 --> 01:10:16.837
Please. forgive me.

1459
01:10:17.796 --> 01:10:18.923
Thank you.

1460
01:10:20.925 --> 01:10:23.135
Thank you for apologizing. Martín.

1461
01:10:26.347 --> 01:10:28.641
I know apologies
aren't easy for you. [chuckles]

1462
01:10:28.724 --> 01:10:30.059
No. they aren't.

1463
01:10:31.560 --> 01:10:34.104
You're right. they're not.
but you know why I'm doing this.

1464
01:10:35.147 --> 01:10:37.149
You're the love of my life.

1465
01:10:38.108 --> 01:10:39.401
That's why.

1466
01:10:40.277 --> 01:10:41.362
[sighs. kisses]

1467
01:10:41.445 --> 01:10:42.655
Fuck.

1468
01:10:43.405 --> 01:10:44.615
Thank you.

1469
01:10:45.616 --> 01:10:46.992
Thank you for…

1470
01:10:47.785 --> 01:10:50.287
for seeing me.
for giving me one more chance…

1471
01:10:50.371 --> 01:10:51.205
Thank you.

1472
01:10:52.081 --> 01:10:54.583
I never said I was giving you
one more chance.

1473
01:10:58.087 --> 01:10:59.171
Well. but…

1474
01:10:59.672 --> 01:11:01.048
You… what?

1475
01:11:03.300 --> 01:11:04.385
[sighs]

1476
01:11:06.262 --> 01:11:07.930
Martín. you're a compulsive liar.

1477
01:11:09.014 --> 01:11:12.309
Let's just speak honestly for once.
That's how I met you. lying to your wife.

1478
01:11:12.393 --> 01:11:13.936
And that's fine.

1479
01:11:14.019 --> 01:11:17.189
You know. I'm not perfect.
and I don't expect you to be either.

1480
01:11:17.273 --> 01:11:18.691
We all have our flaws.

1481
01:11:20.109 --> 01:11:23.946
But in a relationship.
there are certain rules

1482
01:11:24.446 --> 01:11:26.907
that you still don't understand.

1483
01:11:26.991 --> 01:11:31.370
And I commend you for coming here today.
That's a huge step for you.

1484
01:11:32.579 --> 01:11:35.291
But you still have so much more to learn.

1485
01:11:37.293 --> 01:11:41.588
And thank you so much for the info on…
on Monterrey.

1486
01:11:42.298 --> 01:11:44.591
[sighs] Sure.

1487
01:11:45.759 --> 01:11:47.720
Sure. yeah. I think it could be useful.

1488
01:11:48.679 --> 01:11:50.180
I'm really glad you stopped by.

1489
01:11:50.264 --> 01:11:54.768
Yeah. me too.
And hey. thanks for your time. Anyway…

1490
01:11:54.852 --> 01:11:56.478
I should get going. Goodbye.

1491
01:11:58.856 --> 01:12:00.607
- Hey. thanks. Thanks.
- Of course. sir.

1492
01:12:00.691 --> 01:12:01.984
- See you.
- Have a great day.

1493
01:12:05.738 --> 01:12:09.199
[Martín] Are you asking me
to let Mexico lose against Iraq?

1494
01:12:10.492 --> 01:12:12.202
[Cañedo] I'm not asking you.

1495
01:12:12.286 --> 01:12:16.206
México <i>will </i>lose to Iraq
and will finish second in its group.

1496
01:12:17.458 --> 01:12:20.544
[sighs] That's the biggest load of crap
I've ever heard. Guillermo.

1497
01:12:21.462 --> 01:12:25.215
Listen. if Mexico comes in first.
they'll go to Monterrey.

1498
01:12:25.299 --> 01:12:27.634
Azteca Stadium is Emilio Azcárraga's.

1499
01:12:28.135 --> 01:12:31.430
The national team only plays
in his stadium.

1500
01:12:31.513 --> 01:12:33.599
What part of that don't you understand?

1501
01:12:35.059 --> 01:12:37.644
[Martín] They don't want the team playing
anywhere but the Azteca.

1502
01:12:39.229 --> 01:12:40.814
[Bora] And what do you want Martín?

1503
01:12:42.733 --> 01:12:44.943
I want you to score five goals.

1504
01:12:45.027 --> 01:12:46.779
[intense music playing]

1505
01:12:46.862 --> 01:12:49.323
I refuse to let our team lose
this World Cup.

1506
01:12:52.743 --> 01:12:53.744
Okay.

1507
01:12:54.912 --> 01:12:56.455
I respect you. Martín.

1508
01:12:58.791 --> 01:13:01.960
I respect the hell
out of you too. Bora. [chuckles]

1509
01:13:02.586 --> 01:13:03.670
[sighs]

1510
01:13:05.422 --> 01:13:07.383
They were gonna offer you a house.

1511
01:13:07.466 --> 01:13:08.634
Wait. a house?

1512
01:13:10.344 --> 01:13:11.345
You're joking.

1513
01:13:12.471 --> 01:13:14.348
[laughs] I was fucking with you.

1514
01:13:14.431 --> 01:13:17.393
- [Bora] You asshole.
- They weren't gonna offer you shit.

1515
01:13:17.476 --> 01:13:21.271
[laughs] Hey. if you win this World Cup.
I'll fucking marry you.

1516
01:13:21.355 --> 01:13:23.273
I'll buy you a house.
I'll get you a minivan.

1517
01:13:23.357 --> 01:13:26.235
[Martín] <i>Okay. we didn't score</i>
<i>five goals. but we did score one.</i>

1518
01:13:26.318 --> 01:13:29.279
<i>And with that. we finished first</i>
<i>in the group. undefeated.</i>

1519
01:13:29.363 --> 01:13:31.323
[José Ramón] <i>After their victory</i>
<i>against Iraq.</i>

1520
01:13:31.407 --> 01:13:34.535
<i>Mexico plays</i>
<i>their fourth match against Bulgaria.</i>

1521
01:13:34.618 --> 01:13:38.288
<i>Past the 35-minute mark.</i>
<i>Amador with the touch.</i>

1522
01:13:38.372 --> 01:13:39.665
<i>Sets up Negrete.</i>

1523
01:13:39.748 --> 01:13:41.250
<i>He plays it to Aguirre.</i>

1524
01:13:41.333 --> 01:13:42.918
<i>What a volley by El Vasco.</i>

1525
01:13:43.001 --> 01:13:46.130
<i>Back it goes to Negrete.</i>
<i>Here he comes. The scissor kick!</i>

1526
01:13:46.213 --> 01:13:49.091
<i>Goal! Negrete scores!</i>

1527
01:13:49.174 --> 01:13:50.384
No fucking way.

1528
01:13:50.467 --> 01:13:53.387
- [coughs] No way. Manuel!
- ['80s pop playing]

1529
01:13:53.470 --> 01:13:55.514
Oh! Oh! Oh! [exclaims]

1530
01:13:55.597 --> 01:13:56.890
Goal!

1531
01:13:56.974 --> 01:14:01.019
Goal. motherfucker! Goal. Oh. fuck yeah!

1532
01:14:01.103 --> 01:14:03.856
[José Ramón] <i>The best goal in this Cup.</i>
<i>Mexico is celebrating.</i>

1533
01:14:03.939 --> 01:14:07.985
<i>For the first time ever.</i>
<i>the team advances to a fifth game.</i>

1534
01:14:08.068 --> 01:14:10.821
<i>the quarterfinals. and now Mexico</i>
<i>faces West Germany</i>

1535
01:14:10.904 --> 01:14:12.322
<i>in Monterrey in what will surely be</i>

1536
01:14:12.406 --> 01:14:15.784
<i>the most important match</i>
<i>in the nation's football history.</i>

1537
01:14:15.868 --> 01:14:17.578
[singing anthem]

1538
01:14:17.661 --> 01:14:19.663
[crowd cheering]

1539
01:14:20.873 --> 01:14:22.040
Come on!

1540
01:14:22.124 --> 01:14:23.959
[energetic music playing]

1541
01:14:24.042 --> 01:14:26.712
[José Ramón] <i>The whistle blows.</i>
<i>and the quarterfinal is underway.</i>

1542
01:14:26.795 --> 01:14:29.131
<i>Mexico against West Germany.</i>

1543
01:14:30.424 --> 01:14:33.177
<i>The Mexican team has been outstanding.</i>

1544
01:14:33.260 --> 01:14:35.596
<i>dominating the last Cup's runner-up</i>
<i>with a brilliant display.</i>

1545
01:14:35.679 --> 01:14:37.014
Come on. México!

1546
01:14:37.097 --> 01:14:39.224
<i>El Abuelo Cruz inside the box.</i>

1547
01:14:39.308 --> 01:14:42.227
<i>- It's in. Mexico scores!</i>
- Yeah!

1548
01:14:42.311 --> 01:14:43.729
- [whistle blows]
<i>- Hold on.</i>

1549
01:14:43.812 --> 01:14:45.272
That's our call.

1550
01:14:45.355 --> 01:14:47.649
[José Ramón] <i>The referee</i>
<i>calls a prior foul in the area.</i>

1551
01:14:47.733 --> 01:14:49.359
<i>and Mexico is left without a goal.</i>

1552
01:14:50.068 --> 01:14:51.653
<i>The match intensifies.</i>

1553
01:14:51.737 --> 01:14:53.572
Hugo! Drop back. Take it!

1554
01:14:53.655 --> 01:14:57.367
<i>The Mexican team standing firm.</i>
<i>holding its ground. pressing forward.</i>

1555
01:14:58.535 --> 01:15:02.539
<i>Ninety minutes gone. and still no goals.</i>

1556
01:15:02.623 --> 01:15:04.416
[whistle blows]

1557
01:15:04.500 --> 01:15:07.127
[José Ramón] <i>The referee blows the whistle</i>
<i>for full time.</i>

1558
01:15:07.211 --> 01:15:09.463
<i>and we're headed to penalties. folks.</i>

1559
01:15:09.546 --> 01:15:13.759
<i>Bora has two reliable takers.</i>
<i>Manuel Negrete and Hugo Sánchez.</i>

1560
01:15:13.842 --> 01:15:16.345
<i>But hang on. Our Pichichi is in trouble.</i>

1561
01:15:16.428 --> 01:15:17.679
<i>He's been cramping for a while.</i>

1562
01:15:17.763 --> 01:15:19.890
<i>and it's unclear</i>
<i>if he'll be able to take the penalty.</i>

1563
01:15:19.973 --> 01:15:22.184
- He's gonna stay on the ground.
- I think so too.

1564
01:15:22.267 --> 01:15:23.393
- He's gonna stay?
- Mm-hm.

1565
01:15:23.477 --> 01:15:24.353
Little bitch.

1566
01:15:24.436 --> 01:15:26.647
Hugo won't get up. I bet he won't.

1567
01:15:27.272 --> 01:15:30.901
- [sighs] Pfft.
- [crowd chanting]

1568
01:15:30.984 --> 01:15:33.153
- That bastard's gotta shoot.
- I don't think he will.

1569
01:15:33.237 --> 01:15:35.989
No. he <i>will </i>stand up.
Of course he fucking will.

1570
01:15:36.073 --> 01:15:37.449
I'll be back. I'll be right back.

1571
01:15:37.533 --> 01:15:39.535
[intense music playing]

1572
01:15:44.081 --> 01:15:46.750
[indistinct chatter]

1573
01:15:46.833 --> 01:15:48.919
Hey. buddy. Hey. Hey.

1574
01:15:49.002 --> 01:15:50.837
- I need your jacket. man.
- I'm sorry?

1575
01:15:50.921 --> 01:15:52.548
That jacket. Give it to me.

1576
01:15:54.299 --> 01:15:56.343
- That's it. nice and slow.
- Hugo. You're the man.

1577
01:15:56.426 --> 01:15:58.845
What a game. man. We almost had 'em.

1578
01:15:58.929 --> 01:16:02.849
This is your moment. This is it.
Did you pick your penalty already?

1579
01:16:02.933 --> 01:16:04.685
- [grunts] I wish I could. but--
- But what?

1580
01:16:04.768 --> 01:16:05.769
I can't do it.

1581
01:16:05.852 --> 01:16:07.521
- Why not?
- It's what's best for the team.

1582
01:16:07.604 --> 01:16:09.773
- Huh?
- I'm cramped up. There's no way.

1583
01:16:09.856 --> 01:16:11.525
It's what's best for which team?

1584
01:16:11.608 --> 01:16:14.027
'Cause I don't see you cramping up
like this for Real Madrid.

1585
01:16:14.111 --> 01:16:16.029
What about Real Madrid?
Stop fucking around. Hugo.

1586
01:16:16.113 --> 01:16:18.240
I'm not fucking around. man.

1587
01:16:18.323 --> 01:16:20.117
What. you're trying
to lecture me now? Huh?

1588
01:16:20.200 --> 01:16:23.495
First time you set foot on a pitch.
and you're fucking lecturing me?

1589
01:16:23.579 --> 01:16:26.248
The fuck you know about football?
Little man.

1590
01:16:27.874 --> 01:16:30.210
- [Martín] Bora.
- What are you doing here. man?

1591
01:16:30.294 --> 01:16:31.837
How come Hugo doesn't want to kick. huh?

1592
01:16:31.920 --> 01:16:33.714
The whole team is scared shitless.

1593
01:16:33.797 --> 01:16:36.758
I don't have Tomás. I don't have Javier.
and now I don't have Hugo.

1594
01:16:36.842 --> 01:16:39.886
- The guys don't want to do it.
- It's their fucking job. Bora!

1595
01:16:39.970 --> 01:16:42.598
Choose the most decent kickers you have
and force them to do it.

1596
01:16:42.681 --> 01:16:45.225
Listen to me. I know how this goes. okay?

1597
01:16:45.309 --> 01:16:48.061
If I force them. they fail.
They have to want to kick.

1598
01:16:49.605 --> 01:16:50.814
And get out of here.

1599
01:16:52.524 --> 01:16:54.067
Raúl. Raúl. you're not shooting?

1600
01:16:54.151 --> 01:16:55.819
Only if coach tells me to.

1601
01:16:55.902 --> 01:16:59.156
Raúl. people will remember you
if you decide for yourself.

1602
01:16:59.239 --> 01:17:02.284
Who scored the most beautiful goal
at the World Cup. man? Huh? Come on.

1603
01:17:02.367 --> 01:17:05.579
Who's been the best player
on this damn team. Fernando? Tell me.

1604
01:17:05.662 --> 01:17:07.039
Everyone's here to see <i>you</i>. man!

1605
01:17:07.122 --> 01:17:08.540
Are you a leader or a follower?

1606
01:17:08.624 --> 01:17:11.251
History only remembers the ones
who make their penalties.

1607
01:17:11.335 --> 01:17:12.794
Don't fuck this up. Raise your hand.

1608
01:17:12.878 --> 01:17:16.256
Fucking Raúl's already volunteered.
You're gonna look like an asshole.

1609
01:17:17.299 --> 01:17:18.258
Hey. coach.

1610
01:17:18.759 --> 01:17:19.843
I'll take the first one.

1611
01:17:19.926 --> 01:17:22.054
Okay. fine. Good luck. You got this.

1612
01:17:22.137 --> 01:17:24.306
[Raúl] Coach. I'll go.

1613
01:17:24.389 --> 01:17:26.141
- Come. That's great. Good.
- Nice. Good job.

1614
01:17:26.224 --> 01:17:29.061
[Martín] And suddenly.
we had our penalty takers.

1615
01:17:29.144 --> 01:17:33.148
Now. if Bora could just cast his magic.
we'd beat West Germany.

1616
01:17:33.231 --> 01:17:34.524
Listen to me. men.

1617
01:17:36.068 --> 01:17:38.070
You and I. we're not the same.

1618
01:17:38.695 --> 01:17:40.906
I wasn't born in México.

1619
01:17:40.989 --> 01:17:44.493
But this is the place that I chose.

1620
01:17:44.576 --> 01:17:49.790
You want to know why?
Because here. anything is possible.

1621
01:17:49.873 --> 01:17:52.501
And I know it's possible
to beat West Germany.

1622
01:17:52.584 --> 01:17:54.336
- And whoever the fuck we want.
- Yeah.

1623
01:17:54.419 --> 01:17:56.922
